    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.26.44a" />
                <note type="curatorial">90-1 Aly Collection</note>
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>
                Columbia, Rt. 5.<lb/>
                12-15-'59
                </dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Bower:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>As you know, I wrote Lucile that I'd like to visit at your home from about Dec. 26 to around Jan. 1. That is the only free time I can see ahead before next summer, and we have a lot to do, I feel, before Lucile begins writing on the biography. She says for me to come on, that Gramby will be there, but you will be in 
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.26.44b"/>
                <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                
                Washington! I wonder, is Fate trying to be funny? Last time you were in the hospital. This time, 
                <hi rend="underline">if</hi> I come, are you to be on the other side of the continent?</p>
               
               <p>This is the point of my note: Do you plan to be away <hi rend="underline">all that time</hi>? Would I miss you entirely?</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Affectionately</salute>
                <signed>John</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">44</fw>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
